metadata.name: GRAVITATE #14
metadata.description:
Each piece in this collection is made from the simple concept of layering grids of circles. The varying grid sizes, circle sizes, positions and colors combine to create interesting dithering effects. There are seven color palettes in the algorithm and these range from low contrast, muted palettes (e.g. Mystic Sands) to high contrast, super saturated palettes (e.g. Inferno).

- - -

GRAVITATE is my first generative art collection and was made using only p5.js.

- - -

Commands:
Press `1` to save a low-res PNG 1200x1800
Press `2` to save a high-res PNG 4800x7200

Note that it may take up to 10secs for the image render to complete.

metadata.name: Monochrome Intersections #109
metadata.description:
I decided to do this version because Intersections created too many issues with the previews. I made a reserve list for all collectors of Intersections (this reserve list will be available during 1 week). I put a small price because of preview‚Äôs issues and I am really grateful to saw all my projects found collectors, and I don‚Äôt know how to tell you üôè
‚Ä®I also worked on a bug to fix the rendering on objkt.com.‚Ä®

Monochrome Intersections are a group of artworks creating organic and animated lines. A mix between digital renderings with colorful lines and a generated grid creating a paper-like visual.

Lines are animated with an infinite algorithm to create a mesmerizing animation. 
The pieces's size, position and frequency are generated for each token, along with the colour theme and the composition effect. 

You can click to play/pause the animation.

Features :
- Clip: triangle, circle or reversed triangle
- LinesCount: number of lines
- smallLines: boolean, if lines are thin or bold
- colorTheme: name of the color theme
- filter: Canvas composition effect applied : difference, multiply, xor, hard-light, source-over
- isDistorted: distortions enabled

‚Ä®Handmade by code with Javascript, made with fragment.tools
Quentin Hocd√©, Brussels (Belgium), 2023.

metadata.name: No Writing on Walls #45
metadata.description:
"No Writing on Walls," is a visual representation of the concept of writing on walls as a form of self-expression. The abstract wall covered in graffiti and positive words serves to showcase the diverse voices and messages that people want to share, despite the restriction against writing on walls. My aim was to challenge the negative stereotypes associated with graffiti and demonstrate the beauty and creativity that can arise when people are allowed to express themselves freely. With this artwork, I hope to spark reflection and encourage viewers to consider the power of self-expression and its impact on individuals and society.
- Look for the gold mode
- press p so export png
- press s to export svg

metadata.name: Rangxel #688
Supernal Memories #217
metadata.description:
With its layered bursts of color, light, and shadow, Supernal Memories carries an underlying message of optimism through its harmony of seeming dualities ‚Äì hard and soft, familiar and surprising, expression and introspection.

Each newly generated circle brings its own energy, creating layered groups of light that sometimes resemble phenomena like nebula, lightning sprites, and auras ‚Äì ethereal whispers of something remembered. 

Supernal Memories is an invitation to observe the forms & feel of each piece without labeling their qualities, to contemplate the infinite possibilities of the universe, and to explore the depths of your imagination.


--

Created by Diego Pintos @DondiegoTez
Creative collaboration with Tender @tender_art

To get a high resolution file, add "&print=14000" to the end of the live URL / hash, using any resolution number that fits your needs. Press 's' to save the file when it is done loading.

Press 'p' to continue the animation for another variation.

100% code, made with p5.js

metadata.name: There And Then #93
metadata.description:
This project draws inspiration from the dynamic and exploratory ethos of Hic Et Nunc's early days, when artists were venturing into the possibilities of NFTs and pushing creative boundaries.

The color palettes were inadvertently provided by some talented artists who had originally intended them for another project, which was ultimately completed but never published.
Harvey McFly is to blame for the leak.

The color palettes have been paired together, creating an unexpected chromatic collaboration between the artists.

I have chosen to mint this project from TheWallet, as it represents one of the most intriguing experiments ever conducted on a blockchain.

This is the inaugural work to be published on fx(hash) through TheWallet, and I hope that other artists will follow suit and engage in this playful and nonsensical practice in the future.

A special thanks goes out to @TheWalletNft, who suggested the idea of minting on fx(hash) and handled the profile setup on the site.

The open and collaborative nature of TheWallet allows anyone with the seed phrase to modify the sale and to publish any kind of content from TheWallet. For this reason this profile is not, and should never be verified by fx(hash) and collectors should pay extra caution when collecting from it.

Yours, CCDDBB

Hand coded with love. üíö
Powered by p5 and chroma.
